questions.explanation:
&lt;p data-end=&quot;36&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;34&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 2 i.e,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;A-i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;i, B-iv, C-i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;, D-i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;36&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul data-end=&quot;699&quot; data-start=&quot;56&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;190&quot; data-start=&quot;56&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;190&quot; data-start=&quot;58&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;87&quot; data-start=&quot;58&quot;&gt;Jat Rebellion (1669&amp;nbsp;A.D.)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;During the reign of Aurangzeb, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Jats revolted in 1669&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;under the leadership of Gokul Jat&lt;/span&gt;, the Zamindar of Tilpat.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Mughal army defeated Gokul and sentenced him to death.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;The second Jat rebellion was led by Rajaram Jat.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Rajaram killed the Mughal general and plundered Akbar&amp;rsquo;s tomb at Sikandra.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;According to historian Manuchi,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Rajaram dug up Akbar&amp;rsquo;s bones and burnt them.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;But&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;in 1688, Rajaram was defeated&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and killed in a battle.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;The third Jat rebellion was led by Churaman&lt;/span&gt;, nephew of Rajaram, which could not be suppressed because Aurangzeb was engaged in southern expansion at this time. Eventually, the Jats, under the leadership of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Suraj Mal established a state called Bharatpur.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;328&quot; data-start=&quot;191&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;328&quot; data-start=&quot;193&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;226&quot; data-start=&quot;193&quot;&gt;Bundela Rebellion (1675 A.D.)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;261&quot; data-start=&quot;130&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p data-end=&quot;261&quot; data-start=&quot;132&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong data-end=&quot;157&quot; data-start=&quot;136&quot;&gt;Bundela Rebellion&lt;/strong&gt; was a significant revolt against the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;212&quot; data-start=&quot;195&quot;&gt;Mughal Empire&lt;/strong&gt;, particularly during the reign of &lt;strong data-end=&quot;260&quot; data-start=&quot;247&quot;&gt;Aurangzeb&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;456&quot; data-start=&quot;265&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p data-end=&quot;456&quot; data-start=&quot;267&quot;&gt;It was &lt;strong data-end=&quot;314&quot; data-start=&quot;274&quot;&gt;initially led by Champat Rai Bundela&lt;/strong&gt;, a prominent Bundela chieftain, who opposed Mughal dominance in the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;405&quot; data-start=&quot;383&quot;&gt;Bundelkhand region&lt;/strong&gt; (in present-day Madhya Pradesh and Uttar Pradesh).&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;631&quot; data-start=&quot;458&quot;&gt;
		&lt;p data-end=&quot;631&quot; data-start=&quot;460&quot;&gt;After the death of Champat Rai (who was eventually killed in a skirmish with the Mughals), the resistance was &lt;strong data-end=&quot;630&quot; data-start=&quot;570&quot;&gt;continued and intensified by his son, Chhatrasal Bundela&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;510&quot; data-start=&quot;329&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;510&quot; data-start=&quot;331&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;429&quot; data-start=&quot;331&quot;&gt;Satnami Rebellion (1672 A.D. &amp;rarr; but more accurately 1672, some sources link 1669 A.D. as start)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Satnami were&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;people of an agricultural community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His residence area was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Narnaul&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reason for their rebellion was a fight between a soldier and a farmer&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;in 1672 AD&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and a rebellion started in the region, but the Mughal Empire soon suppressed this rebellion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;699&quot; data-start=&quot;511&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;699&quot; data-start=&quot;513&quot;&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Mughal-Sikh conflict&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This was the only rebellion of his time, which took place for religious reasons.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Sikh rebellion mainly started after the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;execution of Guru Teg Bahadur in 1675 AD.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;After the death of Guru Teg Bahadur,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Guru Gobind Singh always opposed Aurangzeb&amp;rsquo;s bigoted policies&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He made his headquarters at Anandapur.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Guru Gobind Singh had abolished the throne of Guru even before his death and played&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;his role in making Sikhs a fanatic&amp;nbsp;sect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;After Aurangzeb&amp;rsquo;s death, his successor Bahadur Shah made a treaty with Guru Gobind Singh and the Guru supported him in the wars in South India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amazon Basin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Amazon Basin&lt;/strong&gt; is the largest drainage basin in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It covers an area of approximately &lt;strong&gt;7 million square kilometers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The basin spans across multiple countries in South America, including &lt;strong&gt;Brazil, Peru, Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Venezuela, and Guyana&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Amazon River, which runs through the basin, is the &lt;strong&gt;second longest river&lt;/strong&gt; in the world and carries the largest volume of water.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The basin is known for its &lt;strong&gt;rich biodiversity&lt;/strong&gt; and is home to the Amazon Rainforest, which is often referred to as the &amp;quot;lungs of the Earth.&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Amazon Rainforest&lt;/strong&gt; produces approximately &lt;strong&gt;20% of the world&amp;#39;s oxygen&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The basin plays a crucial role in the global &lt;strong&gt;water cycle&lt;/strong&gt; and climate regulation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is home to an estimated &lt;strong&gt;390 billion individual trees&lt;/strong&gt; and about &lt;strong&gt;16,000 species of plants&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Amazon Basin also supports a diverse range of wildlife, including &lt;strong&gt;jaguars, pink river dolphins, and macaws&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Deforestation and climate change pose significant threats to the Amazon Basin, impacting its ecosystem and biodiversity.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Efforts are being made globally to &lt;strong&gt;conserve and protect&lt;/strong&gt; this vital region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behramji Malabari&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Behramji Malabari was an Indian poet, publicist, and social reformer born on 18th May 1853.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He played a pivotal role in advocating for the rights of women, especially in his campaign against child marriage and for the passage of the Age of Consent Act, 1891.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Malabari&amp;#39;s efforts brought attention to the plight of young girls who were subjected to early marriage and its detrimental effects on their health and well-being.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;His activism and writings were instrumental in influencing the British authorities to raise the age of consent for girls from 10 to 12 years through the Age of Consent Act, 1891.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Age of Consent Act, 1891&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Age of Consent Act, 1891 was a legislation enacted during the British colonial rule in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Act raised the age of consent for sexual intercourse for girls from 10 to 12 years.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This was one of the early legal reforms aimed at protecting young girls from exploitation and child marriage.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Act was a significant milestone in the history of social reforms in India, highlighting the growing awareness and efforts towards improving women&amp;#39;s rights and conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Behramji Malabari&amp;#39;s Contributions&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Besides his work on the Age of Consent Act, Malabari was also known for his efforts in social reforms such as widow remarriage and the fight against the practice of purdah (veil).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He founded the &amp;quot;Seva Sadan&amp;quot; in 1885, an institution dedicated to the welfare of women and children.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Malabari&amp;#39;s literary works, including his poetry and publicist writings, played a crucial role in spreading social awareness and advocating for reforms.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;His book, &amp;quot;Notes on Infant Marriage and Enforced Widowhood,&amp;quot; published in 1887, was influential in bringing the issues of child marriage and enforced widowhood to the forefront of social discourse.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Particulate matter of size 2.5 &amp;mu;m and less&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PM2.5 stands for particulate matter with a diameter of 2.5 micrometers or smaller.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These fine particles are capable of penetrating deep into the respiratory tract and reaching the lungs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PM2.5 is often generated from combustion processes, including motor vehicles, power plants, and wildfires.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;High levels of PM2.5 are associated with adverse health effects, including respiratory and cardiovascular diseases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Due to their small size, PM2.5 particles remain suspended in the air for longer periods, increasing the likelihood of inhalation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Air Quality Index (AQI):&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An index used to communicate how polluted the air currently is or how polluted it is forecast to become.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;PM2.5 is one of the pollutants measured to determine the AQI.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sources of PM2.5:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Natural sources: Wildfires, volcanic eruptions, and dust storms.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Anthropogenic sources: Vehicle emissions, industrial processes, and fossil fuel combustion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Impacts:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Short-term exposure: Irritation of the eyes, nose, and throat; coughing; shortness of breath.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Long-term exposure: Aggravation of asthma, development of bronchitis, and increased risk of heart disease.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preventive Measures:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Wearing masks designed to filter out PM2.5 particles.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Using air purifiers indoors to reduce exposure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reducing outdoor activities when PM2.5 levels are high.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To redo the last action&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CTRL + Y&lt;/strong&gt; is a shortcut in Microsoft Word that is used to &lt;strong&gt;redo the last action&lt;/strong&gt; that was undone.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This is particularly useful when you have undone an action using &lt;strong&gt;CTRL + Z&lt;/strong&gt; (which is the shortcut for undo) and then decide that you want to redo the action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1: To undo a bullet&lt;/strong&gt; - This is incorrect. To undo a bullet, you would typically use the &amp;quot;Backspace&amp;quot; key or the &amp;quot;Decrease Indent&amp;quot; button.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2: To undo the last action&lt;/strong&gt; - This is incorrect. The shortcut for undoing the last action is &lt;strong&gt;CTRL + Z&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4: Create a bullet list&lt;/strong&gt; - This is incorrect. To create a bullet list, you can use the shortcut &lt;strong&gt;CTRL + Shift + L&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cabinet includes senior ministers, while the Council includes all categories of ministers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Cabinet is a smaller body within the Council of Ministers, composed of senior ministers holding important portfolios such as Finance, Defence, and Home Affairs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Council of Ministers consists of three categories: Cabinet Ministers, Ministers of State, and Deputy Ministers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Cabinet is the decision-making body responsible for major policies and key issues, while the Council of Ministers assists in broader governmental functions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Prime Minister is part of both the Cabinet and the Council of Ministers, serving as the head of the government.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Cabinet exercises executive authority and is collectively responsible to the Parliament, particularly the Lok Sabha.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Ministers:&lt;/strong&gt; These are senior members of the Council of Ministers who head important ministries like Finance, Defence, Home, External Affairs, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ministers of State:&lt;/strong&gt; These are junior ministers who either work independently or assist Cabinet Ministers in their duties.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deputy Ministers:&lt;/strong&gt; They assist both Cabinet Ministers and Ministers of State in their specific responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strongcollective strong=&quot;&quot;&gt; The Council of Ministers, including the Cabinet, is collectively responsible to the Lok Sabha as per Article 75 of the Indian Constitution.&lt;/strongcollective&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prime Minister&amp;#39;s Role:&lt;/strong&gt; The Prime Minister leads the Cabinet and the Council of Ministers, acts as the chief advisor to the President, and coordinates the functioning of all ministries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;Scanner.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A scanner is a device that converts printed documents into Digital Images.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It captures images from photographic prints, posters, magazine pages, and similar sources for computer editing and display.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A scanner uses light-sensing equipment to read the image or text on the physical document and converts it into a set of image files that can be stored, viewed, edited, and shared electronically.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Scanners can handle various types of materials ranging from photographs and documents to thicker materials like books. Some specialized scanners can even scan 3D objects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The digitized image can be saved in various file formats (like .jpg, .png, or .tif for images, or .pdf for documents). Many scanners also come with Optical Character Recognition (OCR) software that can convert scanned documents into editable text files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harisena&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Allahabad pillar inscription was composed by &lt;strong&gt;Harisena&lt;/strong&gt;, who was a court poet and the chief minister of Samudragupta.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This inscription is a eulogy (Prashasti) and provides details about the military conquests and achievements of &lt;strong&gt;Samudragupta&lt;/strong&gt;, the Gupta Emperor.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is written in classical Sanskrit and inscribed in the script of &lt;strong&gt;Brahmi&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The pillar highlights Samudragupta&amp;#39;s extensive campaigns, mentioning his victories over rulers in North India and his influence over rulers in South India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The inscription also emphasizes Samudragupta&amp;rsquo;s qualities as a ruler, showcasing him as a skilled warrior, a patron of art and culture, and a benevolent ruler.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vishakhadatta&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Vishakhadatta was an ancient Indian playwright and poet known for his famous Sanskrit play &lt;strong&gt;Mudrarakshasa&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mudrarakshasa is a political drama that narrates the story of the rise of Chandragupta Maurya to power with the help of Chanakya.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He lived during the Gupta period but is not related to the Allahabad pillar inscription.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aryabhata&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aryabhata was a renowned Indian mathematician and astronomer of ancient times.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He is famous for his works like the &lt;strong&gt;Aryabhatiya&lt;/strong&gt;, which discusses mathematics, astronomy, and spherical trigonometry.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He contributed significantly to the understanding of the value of pi, the concept of zero, and the heliocentric theory of the solar system.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, Aryabhata was not associated with the composition of the Allahabad pillar inscription.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Amarasimha&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Amarasimha was an ancient Indian scholar and lexicographer, best known for his Sanskrit thesaurus &lt;strong&gt;Amarakosha&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Amarakosha is a significant work in Sanskrit literature, containing a comprehensive list of synonyms and vocabulary.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;He was one of the nine gems (Navaratnas) in the court of King Chandragupta II, a later Gupta ruler.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Amarasimha did not contribute to the Allahabad pillar inscription.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tropical belts&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;include desert and semidesert landscapes on the continents and of high water temperatures and high salinity in the ocean.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are two important latitudes&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;23&amp;frac12;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;deg;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;North&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the tropic of&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Cancer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;23&amp;frac12;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;deg;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;South&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the tropic of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Capricorn.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;area&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;lying between these&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;two tropics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;known as the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;tropical region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, it is clear that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rom the tropic of Cancer to the tropic of Capricorn&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;extension of the tropical belt.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The region lying&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;5&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;10 degrees&lt;/span&gt;, north and south of Tropic of cancer and the Tropic of Capricorn is known as&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subtropical Region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some of the areas that lie in the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subtropical region&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;across the globe are
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The Northern Part of India&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Parts of South America&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Certain parts of Northern Australia&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ​&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The region between&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;5&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;10&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;degree is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;near the Equator&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is called the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Equatorial Region&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Industrial Policy Statement of 1956.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Industrial policy statement of 1956 was regarded as the &lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Economic Constitution of India&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;The Bible of State Capitalism&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 1956 Policy &lt;strong&gt;empha&amp;shy;sised on:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Need to expand the public sector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To build up a large and growing coop&amp;shy;erative sector and &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to encourage the separation of ownership and management in private in&amp;shy;dustries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prevent the rise of pri&amp;shy;vate monopolies.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It provided the &lt;strong&gt;basic framework &lt;/strong&gt;for the government&amp;rsquo;s policy in regard to in&amp;shy;dustries till June 1991.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-left:36.0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Classification of industries into three categories:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule A:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It consisted of &lt;strong&gt;17 industries and was&lt;/strong&gt; the&lt;strong&gt; exclusive responsibility of the State&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Out of these, four industries, namely &lt;strong&gt;arms and ammunition, atomic en&amp;shy;ergy, railways, and air transport had Central Government monopolies.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;New units in the remaining industries were developed by the State Governments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule B:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It consisted of&lt;strong&gt; 12 industries that &lt;/strong&gt;were &lt;strong&gt;open to both the private and public sectors, &lt;/strong&gt;however, such industries were &lt;strong&gt;progressively State-owned.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule C:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;All the other industries not included in these two Schedules constituted the third category which was left&lt;strong&gt; open to the pri&amp;shy;vate sector. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;However, the &lt;strong&gt;State reserved the right to undertake any type of indus&amp;shy;trial production.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The IPR 1956, stressed the &lt;strong&gt;importance of cottage and small scale industries&lt;/strong&gt; for &lt;strong&gt;expand&amp;shy;ing employment opportunities&lt;/strong&gt; and wider &lt;strong&gt;decentralization of economic power&lt;/strong&gt; and activity&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Resolution also called for &lt;strong&gt;efforts to maintain industrial peace;&lt;/strong&gt; a fair share of the proceeds of production was to be given to the toiling masses in keeping with the avowed &lt;strong&gt;objectives of democratic socialism.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Criticism&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The IPR 1956 came in for sharp criticism from the private sector since this Resolution &lt;strong&gt;reduced the scope for the expan&amp;shy;sion of the private sector significantly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
The sector was &lt;strong&gt;kept under state control through a system of licenses.&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kitab ul-Hind&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; is the famous book written by the scholar Al-Biruni.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Al-Biruni was a Persian historian, mathematician, and astronomer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;His other works include Kitab al-Tafhim,&amp;nbsp;Bhārata: Ala-Birūnī Al-Biruni, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

